The paper discusses the use of Answer Set Programming (ASP) for problem solving, which falls under the category of Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI). The paper specifically focuses on the handling of preferences between rules, which is a topic related to logic and reasoning (cs.LO) and programming languages (cs.PL). The use of DLV, an efficient engine for ASP, is also discussed, which falls under the category of Logic in Computer Science (cs.LO) and Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC). Finally, the paper discusses the use of meta-interpreters for more efficient computations, which falls under the category of Software Engineering (cs.SE).
